<subSubSection id="185C6FC459C72AB29C6005CC4D04209A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="5E34F483F0C6FD516486B8235A5F79E8" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4C273EBC335319C9B44957084B2D5B18" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Body length: male 10.5-11 mm, female 11-12 mm. The basally constricted abdomen, absence of a golden pilose triangle on the mesoscutum, and partially infuscated wings place this species in a group together with 
<taxonomicName id="D7A14A3015E2DE4DC901A7767A1989BD" genus="P." lsidName="P. diaphanus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="diaphanus">
<emphasis id="85EFFA15850A75B358617E5F80827F51" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. diaphanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D1B0A9734A353F0393AB15A62E76223F" genus="P." lsidName="P. hermetia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="hermetia">
<emphasis id="2F49A3B6F2C390DE615DC1BFE12AA42C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. hermetia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A11C3A4B876571CDEBCCF838CEF5E99B" genus="P." lsidName="P. hermetoides" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="hermetoides">
<emphasis id="42C6CF1D21A8F87C8949B15767C3E8AA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. hermetoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Among these species, 
<taxonomicName id="67C6A213674823F80EACC79394715BAD" genus="P." lsidName="P. elongatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="elongatus">
<emphasis id="6EA3A2B1EBFB64F1D27DCE83F362ABA7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. elongatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only one with yellow colouration on the wing: in the male, only the vena spuria is yellow, in the female the yellow parts are more extensive.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
