</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A487B16B2072DFC896EE05F12ED190C8" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="36DF4547EE94E929247AE6E34094CE91" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="48BC19893FC165EA3290D26E28C49A92" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The yellow wing colouration is much more extensive on the female than on the male. Similar sexual dimorphism in wing colouration also occurs in other 
<taxonomicName id="ABE606B39AFED2DE93A35A46140F7FA2" authority="Reemer, 2013" authorityName="Reemer" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Peradon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Peradon" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EDE901A5D9CD81EFD766F12E5AEC92F0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Peradon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, e.g., 
<taxonomicName id="6BA498DCEB45E49CD0EB4D397A4430F3" genus="P." lsidName="P. chrysopygus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="chrysopygus">
<emphasis id="1F9A2E759063BA53C23E27174F480074" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. chrysopygus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="175E94DA8F9DA5061EB29EE79F4CF9ED" genus="P." lsidName="P. flavofascium" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="flavofascium">
<emphasis id="BECECFB0CEE316E49D339005027436EF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. flavofascium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The male from the Brazilian state Amazonas was collected in humid forest along a small stream (
<normalizedToken id="EF019407CCF929BB25F48DEA721F83B6" originalValue="“igarapé”">&quot;igarape&quot;</normalizedToken>
). The female from Amazonas was collected in a 
<normalizedToken id="451665319DEA2D26CB5CBEC5BB009B71" originalValue="“campinarana”">&quot;campinarana&quot;</normalizedToken>
: a type of vegetation occurring in flat, sandy soils prone to waterlogging, usually dominated by thin trees (pers. comm. G.F.G. Miranda).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
